26) Remove Duplicates
Approach-
we will use 2 pointer approach since we were asked to do it in-place
take j = 0 and start for loop from i = 1
if the elements are not equal, we move j ahead by one place FIRST and only then do we move the unique element to jth index.
TC- O(N)

int removeDuplicates(vector<int>& nums) {
        int n = nums.size();
        int j = 0;
        for(int i = 1; i<n; i++){
            if(nums[i] != nums[j]){
                j++;
                nums[j] = nums[i];
            }
        }
        return j+1;
    }
